## AI Agents (Local Backend)

### ImageContextRetrieverAgent
**File:** `backend/agents/` (called from `context_builder.py`)

Takes a screenshot/image (base64) and extracts structured context:
- Screens detected
- UI elements visible
- User flows implied
- Requirements inferred

Returns prose context for each image.

### _SynthAgent
**File:** `backend/main.py` (inline usage)

Synthesises multiple image contexts + text notes into a single cohesive `context_summary` prose paragraph. Also used for feedback-based context refinement (skips image re-analysis).

### TestPlannerAgent
**File:** `backend/agents/test_planner_agent.py`

Generates test cases from feature context. Accepts:
- `context_summary` (feature)
- `project_context` (project-level background)
- `user_feedback` (optional correction to steer generation)

Returns JSON: `{ feature_summary, test_cases[], coverage_notes }`.

Each test case: `{ test_key, title, goal, description, category, priority, expected_result }`.

### OrchestratorAgent
**File:** `backend/agents/orchestrator_agent.py`

Vision-based execution agent. Takes a screenshot + goal + action history, decides what to do next. Supports `left_click`, `type`, `scroll`, `key`, `screenshot`, `wait`, `stuck` (ask for help), `goal_complete`.

**Providers:**
- Claude (Anthropic) — pixel-accurate coordinates, works on any desktop app
- Gemini (Google) — normalized coordinates (0-1000 scale), browser-optimized

