## Coordinate Math (Vision Agent — Critical)

The local backend captures screenshots with `mss` (physical pixels) but window bounds come from macOS APIs in logical points. Gemini returns normalized `[ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax]` in 0–1000 scale.

```python
# 1. Parse Gemini bounding box
ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax = gemini_box   # 0-1000 scale

# 2. Get center in 0-1000 scale
center_x = (xmin + xmax) / 2
center_y = (ymin + ymax) / 2

# 3. Convert to window pixels (local)
local_x = (center_x / 1000) * window_width
local_y = (center_y / 1000) * window_height

# 4. Apply Retina scale factor + offset to global screen coords
scale_factor = screenshot_width / window_bounds_width
global_x = window_left + (local_x / scale_factor)
global_y = window_top  + (local_y / scale_factor)
```

---

## Human Click Pattern (Critical)

Never use instant clicks — always simulate human timing:

```python
pyautogui.moveTo(x, y, duration=0.2)
pyautogui.mouseDown()
time.sleep(0.1)   # debounce
pyautogui.mouseUp()
```

