## Frontend — Reusable Query Hooks

All React Query hooks live in `src/hooks/useProjectsQueries.ts`:

| Hook | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `useProjects()` | List all user projects |
| `useProject(id)` | Single project |
| `useProjectFeatures(projectId)` | List features for a project |
| `useFeatureTestCases(featureId)` | List test cases for a feature |
| `useBuildFeatureContext()` | Mutation: build/rebuild context (SSE) |
| `useGenerateFeatureTests()` | Mutation: generate tests (SSE) |
| `useCreateProject()` | Mutation: create project with AI context (SSE) |
| `useUpdateProjectContext()` | Mutation: update project context (SSE) |

---

## macOS System Requirements

The local backend requires macOS permissions:
- **Screen Recording** — to capture window screenshots via `mss`
- **Accessibility** — to control mouse/keyboard via `pyautogui`

The backend checks for these on startup and emits warnings if missing.
